requirement: The Fault Manager shall transition to an Error state within its Normal state's Error Monitoring region upon receiving an error signal and send a local response request, then return to Error Free when the error is resolved; transition from the Normal state to a Normal-Safe Transition state upon a fault signal and initiate a system response request; from the Normal-Safe Transition state, transition to either the Safe state or back to the Normal state upon system response completion; and transition from the Safe state to the Normal-Safe Transition state upon a recovery signal, then to the Normal state upon subsequent system response completion.

requirement: The system shall compute the required fuel for propulsion using the equation: required fuel = (mass multiplied by the exponential of the required delta v, divided by Isp, multiplied by 9.81) minus mass.

requirement: The system shall compute the required power by summing the average required power multiplied by the time in eclipse divided by the power system efficiency in eclipse and the average required power multiplied by the time in daylight divided by the power system efficiency in daylight, then dividing the result by the percent time in daylight.
 related_elements: nan
 focus_element: <packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Class" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311873198_361556_47775" name="Effective Power Need Analysis Model">

    <specification xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression" xmi:id="_18_0_2_1a82048c_1420311873214_672595_47802">
      <body>required power = ((avg rev power * time in eclipse / efficiency in eclipse) + (avg rev power * time in daylight / efficiency in daylight)) / percent time in daylight</body>
    </specification>
  </ownedRule>

requirement: The system shall perform the mission by concurrently executing Launch S/C and Maintain Spacecraft Operations; then after Launch S/C completes, executing Separate from L/V; then after Separate from L/V completes, concurrently executing Deploy Mechanisms and Control Trajectory; then after Deploy Mechanisms completes, executing Provide Observation Data (which may be interrupted by a signal event); and completing the mission when both Maintain Spacecraft Operations and Control Trajectory have completed, regardless of the state of Provide Observation Data.

requirement: The mission events shall progress through the following sequence: the Launch Ops Facility sends a Power On signal to the Spacecraft and a Launch signal to the Launch Vehicle; the Launch Vehicle sends a Spacecraft Separation Command to the Spacecraft; the Spacecraft deploys its antenna and solar arrays and notifies the Ground Station of each deployment; the Ground Station sends an On Orbit signal to initiate on-orbit operations; and the Ground Station sends a De-orbit Command to the Spacecraft, which then completes the de-orbit maneuver.
